# Create a Pull Request

1. Check `.gitignore` and staged files:
   - Read the `.gitignore` file.
   - Review all files added to this branch so far.
   - If any files should obviously not be committed:
     - Update `.gitignore` accordingly.
     - Remove those files from git.

2. Write the pull request summary:
   - Summarize everything from this conversation.
   - Save the summary to `docs/pr/pr-body-file-<branch-name>.md` (replace `<branch-name>` with the actual branch name).

3. Create the pull request using the `gh` CLI:
   - Use the `gh pr create` command.
   - Fill in the title.
   - Use `--body-file ./docs/pr/pr-body-file-<branch-name>.md` for the body.

Example:
```bash
git push -u origin <branch-name>
gh pr create --title "feat: Enforce normalized, dash-separated, lowercase labels for all shells" --body-file docs/pr-body-file-fix-label-sanitization.md --fill
```
